place.name: TOCKENHAM
place.gazetteerText: TOCKENHAM, a parish in Cricklade district, Wilts; 2¾ miles SW of Wootton-Bassett r. station. Post town, Wootton-Bassett, under Swindon. Acres, 761. Real property, £1,682. Pop., 157. Houses, 36. T. House is the seat of the Buxtons. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Salisbury Value, £283.* Patron, the Lord Chancellor. Charities, £29. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
